 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-wsfj","title":"Alt+S keyboard shortcut for mode cycling","description":"## Purpose
Implement Alt+S to cycle search modes (LEX → SEM → HYB → LEX).

## Key Binding Decision: Alt+S
Why Alt+S instead of F-key?
- F1-F12 are ALL already used:
  - F1: Help, F2: Theme, F3: Agent filter, F4: Workspace filter
  - F5/F6: Time filters, F7: Context, F8: Editor, F9: Match mode
  - F10: Quit, F11: Source filter, F12: Ranking mode
- Alt+S is available and memorable (S = Search mode)
- Alt combinations work in most modern terminals

Potential issue: Some terminals (especially over SSH) may not handle Alt correctly.
Fallback: Users can use CLI --mode flag if Alt doesn't work.

## Behavior
- Press Alt+S → cycle mode
- If switching to SEM/HYB and model not installed:
  - Show install prompt (tui.sem.prompt)
  - Don't change mode until consent given
- If model downloading:
  - Show toast "Model downloading..."
  - Stay on current mode
- If index building after download:
  - Show toast "Building semantic index..."
  - Stay on current mode

## Status Bar Indicator
- `LEX` - default color (current behavior)
- `SEM` - cyan (ML active)
- `SEM*` - cyan with asterisk (hash fallback)
- `HYB` - magenta

## State Persistence
- Save search_mode to config file
- Restore on startup
- Default: Lexical (for backward compatibility)

## Help Screen
Add to F1:
```
SEARCH MODE
  Alt+S      Cycle search mode (Lexical → Semantic → Hybrid)

  Lexical    BM25 full-text search (fast, exact keywords)
  Semantic   Vector similarity (meaning-focused, requires 23MB model)
  Hybrid     RRF fusion of both (best of both worlds)
```

